ðŸ“š Library Management System (C++)

A terminal-based Library Management System built entirely in C++, using object-oriented programming and file handling. This project includes user authentication with password hashing, role-based access (Admin/User), and persistent data storage via text files.

ðŸš€ Features

User Registration & Login (hashed passwords for basic security)

Admin Panel: Add books, issue/return books, manage users

User Panel: View and request books (max 3 issued at a time)

Persistent Storage using file I/O (users.txt, books.txt, issued_books.txt)

ðŸ“‚ File Structure

users.txt: Stores usernames and hashed passwords

books.txt: Stores book titles and ISBNs

issued_books.txt: Stores issued records with book ISBN, username, issue date, and due date

